The paper proposes a machine learning approach for predicting the remaining useful life of machinery and equipment. Specifically, it introduces a structured-effect neural network that combines the interpretability of traditional methods with the flexibility of deep learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the prediction of time-to-failure, which is a common problem in systems and control (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its approach for decision support, which is a topic of interest in software engineering (cs.SE).
